article.description: Micah Seaborn scored 25 points and Monmouth rolled to a 92-74 victory over Iona on Friday night.
article.headline: Micah Seaborn scores 25 points; Monmouth beats Iona 92-74
article.linkText: Micah Seaborn scores 25 points; Monmouth beats Iona 92-74
article.story: WEST LONG BRANCH, N.J. -- Micah Seaborn scored 25 points and Monmouth rolled to a 92-74 victory over Iona on Friday night. Seaborn was 10 of 17 from the floor. Chris Brady and Justin Robinson added 18 points apiece for the Hawks (11-5, 3-2 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference), who snapped a three-game losing skid, their longest since 2014. Iona (9-7, 2-3) has lost four of its last five. Sam Cassell Jr. had 20 points and made five 3-pointers to lead the Gaels. Iona Jordan Washington scored 17 points, and Rickey McGill made just 1 of 8 field goals, but was 9-of-10 shooting from the line and finished with 11 points and five assists. Monmouth had a double-digit lead midway through the first half and led 54-41 at the break. Robinson's 3-pointer with 9:14 to play stretched the Hawks' lead to 20 points.
